            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "A mnemonic stalker can take a full action to travel from the Astral Plane to the Material Plane or vice versa. When not on the Astral Plane, it gains the extraplanar subtype.",
                "name": "Astral Travel",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "As a swift action, the mnemonic stalker can telepathically probe the mind of a creature within 100 feet, seeking concepts and images of a deity the target worships. As part of this action, the mnemonic stalker changes its shape, appearing as that deity. Alternatively, if the creature doesn\u2019t revere a deity, the stalker changes shape into an individual of the creature\u2019s species. Creatures that succeed at a DC 21 Will save recognize the altered shape as false but don\u2019t see the stalker\u2019s true form. The mnemonic stalker can maintain only one such shape at a time. This is a mind-affecting effect.",
                "name": "Deific Mimicry",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "Three times per day, when a creature casts a spell the mnemonic stalker knows, the stalker can take a reaction to consume the spell. The caster expends the spell, but the spell has no effect, and the mnemonic stalker regains one use of a spell-like ability of the same level or lower.",
                "name": "Mnemonic Predation",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su"
            }
